body:
So this is what happens now. Lost a game because we were getting pressured in Bot lane. We asked jungle for help. And all WW would say is &quot;Soon&quot; (one of those &quot;jungle doesnt start till after 6&quot; players)
We struggle to hold onto bot lane and get pressured with no help from jungle. Bot lane is eventually lost. We are losing by double digits (something like 2 v 15). Bot lane is completely gone. 

And then our jungle pulls the self-rightous sh*t &quot;Face your shit&quot;
refusing to surrender and telling us to &quot;use the challenge&quot; 
Meanwhile he gets over 7 kills while the rest of the team barely hangs on or goes negative. And tells us we need to use this as &quot;a learning experience&quot; telling bot lane (which he never helped) we need to &quot;Face your shit&quot; as if it is our fault thier jungler ganked, they pressured, and yet ww never once came to help. And then when the score was around 6 v 23 and the enemy was knocking on our base. WW refused to surrender. In post game went on this moral speech about how us getting our ass kicked and wanting to accept when a match was lost was &quot;Defeatist&quot; and &quot;you need to learn how to handle yourself on your own&quot; &quot;I did this to teach you a lesson, to better yourself&quot; 
&quot;Handle yourself on your own&quot;? On a Team game? 
Thats like playing a chess game where one side has all the pieces, but the other side has the Bishop and pawns missing &quot;Oh you have to learn to win this game on your own&quot; 

Yeah its happening more and more. These people who are so convinced they are above thier team that they get to hand down &quot;challenges&quot; to thier teammates. Climb off your god damn High horse. Its not your place to dictate what challengers or &quot;learning experiences&quot; your team faces. 

RIOT needs to do something about stopping this &quot;Yolo Solo&quot; attitude. This idea that League is 5 SIngle players all on thier own, they just happen to be on the same match. That One player is superior to all the others. I am really getting sick of listening to these coddled children who thinks the whole world revolves around them. That rather than work as a team, the &#039;team&#039; is just there to prop THEM up. 

If you dont understand how a team game works, and you just want to sit there and issue &#039;decrees&#039; to your team from on-high (because you are so far above your team, its not like they are your EQUALS or anything) Then get off a team game and go play a single player game, maybe you can go play checkers with yourself, that way you can have all the pieces to yourself and tell yourself just how AMAZING -YOU- are. 

And yeah, If I see you in game and you act like that,  I WILL let you die. Thats not me griefing at all, I am not like that. Thats me helping to teach you the Humility of defeat. :) So use it as a challenge. Good luck getting fed without a support to keep you alive. It makes a good &quot;learning experience&quot; doesnt it?
